<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n57045a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n57" href="#n57045a">N57 (VI.B.47)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n57all.htm#n57045a"> 45(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Aideen&apos;s / grave </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Inside the desmesne of Lord Howth is a cromlech marking the grave of Aideen, the daughter of Aengus of Ben Edar, who died of grief at the loss of her husband Oscar, son of Ossian, at a battle at Gavra (Gowra) near Tara in the year <year>A.D.</year> 284. This is also the name of a poem by Sir Samuel Ferguson </mm> </dd></dl>
